-- De Longhi May Take Over Nokia’s Romania Facilities, ZF Reports
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-01-23T08:01:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/de-longhi-may-take-over-nokia-s-romania-facilities-zf-reports.html
De Longhi Spa (DLG) , an Italian home
appliances manufacturer, may open a factory in  Romania  by taking
over  Nokia OYJ (NOKIA) ’s facilities in the city of Cluj-Napoca,  Ziarul
Financiar  reported today, citing unidentified market people.  The Cluj county board is negotiating with five companies
over the Nokia facilities after the phone-maker said it will
close its factory, the newspaper reported, citing Alin Tise,
head of the county.  Talks with two of the companies are at an advanced stage,
Tise told the Bucharest-based newspaper, without naming any of
the firms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  